    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-11-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="146" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d146">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 146.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Cheng Tsao Ju</persName>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chinese
                                        Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington, D.
                                    C.</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-11-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 9,
                                1885</date>. (Received Nov. 9.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 7th instant, inclosing two copies of the
                            President’s proclamation providing for the protection of the Chinese
                            residents of Washington Territory.</p>
                <p>I take pleasure in expressing to you, Mr. Secretary, my profound thanks
                            for the prompt efforts of the Government of the United States in
                            suppressing the lawless combinations against the welfare and peace of
                            the Chinese in that Territory.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>CHENG TSAO JU.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
